  <p>Block 6 demystifies climate models. Students decode IPCC projection figures (anomaly time series, scenario comparisons) and learn what models include (radiative physics, ocean circulation, ice dynamics, basic land surface) vs. what they don't (specific cyclone tracks, individual storm intensities, monsoon-onset-day precision). Why different models give different answers: parametrisation choices, grid resolution, feedback assumptions. Critical move: projection vs. prediction.</p>
